The paper deals with equation systems that arise in various stochastic models, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Languages). The use of Newton's method and the analysis of convergence speed suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of threshold and iteration bounds suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
